"}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"story-time-section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Connect to the Book"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Show the book cover. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Today we will reread some pages of "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_emphasis_non-ital","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Nobody Hugs a Cactus"}]},{"type":"text","text":" by Carter Goodrich. We will think about whether Hank understood his feelings and how he changed his behavior."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Use the Clifford Puppet. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Clifford is really good at managing his emotions—he will help us notice how Hank is feeling and what Hank does to manage his feelings."}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Close-Read: Connect to the Mind Builder "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Focus on Counting As you read, help children count items in the story and say how many there are in all."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"pages 10–11"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Let’s look at Hank’s face and listen to what he says. He wasn’t very nice to the tortoise! How could Hank have acted differently to tell the tortoise that he wanted to be left alone? "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_routine_bold","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"(MB)"}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-h